40
00:01:37,329 --> 00:01:38,729
<b><font color="#FF8000">Felicity:</font></b>
I've got something.

41
00:01:38,731 --> 00:01:41,532
Well, not something-something
but something.

42
00:01:42,935 --> 00:01:44,702
That's good work.

43
00:01:44,704 --> 00:01:47,171
I didn't know they
taught Bo staff

44
00:01:47,173 --> 00:01:48,672
at the Central City
police academy.

45
00:01:48,674 --> 00:01:50,607
They don't. My first
uncover assignment was

46
00:01:50,609 --> 00:01:52,710
with a street gang called
the Pilgrims.

47
00:01:52,712 --> 00:01:54,378
They liked
to mess around with it.

48
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:56,380
I'm gonna head home.

49
00:01:56,382 --> 00:01:58,949
Yeah. You found a place
to stay already?

50
00:01:58,951 --> 00:02:00,184
No. I'm, uh,

51
00:02:00,186 --> 00:02:02,019
just staying where
you guys put me up.

52
00:02:02,021 --> 00:02:04,555
HIVE? That's not a home.
It's barely livable.

53
00:02:04,557 --> 00:02:07,157
It's fine.
I don't need much.

54
00:02:07,159 --> 00:02:09,593
See you, man.

55
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:12,529
What do
you guys got?

56
00:02:12,531 --> 00:02:14,431
Well, I have been working
on a location

57
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:15,599
for Claybourne's mistress.

58
00:02:15,601 --> 00:02:17,735
Prometheus' mother.
We find her...

59
00:02:17,737 --> 00:02:19,603
We find the name for
this son of a bitch.

60
00:02:19,605 --> 00:02:21,605
Eh, unfortunately, the--
the son of a bitch's father

61
00:02:21,607 --> 00:02:23,707
went dark after he met with
the pointy head of an arrow

62
00:02:23,709 --> 00:02:26,076
4 years ago,
and mommy went off the grid.

63
00:02:26,078 --> 00:02:27,277
Why would she do that?

64
00:02:27,279 --> 00:02:28,445
Probably because she knows

65
00:02:28,447 --> 00:02:30,147
that he turned into
a serial killing

66
00:02:30,149 --> 00:02:32,282
psychopath nutjob.

67
00:02:32,284 --> 00:02:34,118
Point being
I have been looking for her

68
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,819
for the past 3 months,

69
00:02:35,821 --> 00:02:37,087
but whatever witness protection
program she put herself into,

70
00:02:37,089 --> 00:02:38,255
it is damn good.

71
00:02:38,257 --> 00:02:39,823
What changed
in 3 months?

72
00:02:39,825 --> 00:02:41,225
I've had a breakthrough.

73
00:02:41,227 --> 00:02:42,760
I've narrowed her new home
down to Illinois.

74
00:02:42,762 --> 00:02:44,428
I just need a couple more
days to narrow that down

75
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,797
into an address.

76
00:02:49,034 --> 00:02:50,601
That's fantastic work.

77
00:02:50,603 --> 00:02:51,802
Thank you.
Curtis is coming in.

78
00:02:51,804 --> 00:02:54,605
He's gonna help
with the search.

79
00:03:00,188 --> 00:03:01,779
It's really nice to
have you back.

80
00:03:01,781 --> 00:03:03,647
Well, I could say
the same to you.

81
00:03:03,649 --> 00:03:05,415
I mean, Hub City
and Russia.

82
00:03:05,417 --> 00:03:07,017
You're really racking
up those miles.

83
00:03:07,019 --> 00:03:09,119
- A lot to catch up on.
- Yeah.

84
00:03:09,121 --> 00:03:11,922
Like you
and Susan Williams?

85
00:03:13,125 --> 00:03:14,625
People talk, Ollie,

86
00:03:14,627 --> 00:03:18,595
and, uh, some people
vomit a little.

87
00:03:18,597 --> 00:03:20,764
Thea, you're kind of
insulting someone

88
00:03:20,766 --> 00:03:22,299
that I'm getting
pretty serious about.

89
00:03:22,301 --> 00:03:24,835
Did I mention people
vomit a little?

90
00:03:24,837 --> 00:03:27,204
You don't like Susan because
of how she does her job.

91
00:03:27,206 --> 00:03:28,705
She's good at her job,

92
00:03:28,707 --> 00:03:30,741
and she's a good person.

93
00:03:30,743 --> 00:03:32,142
So there.

94
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:34,978
Uh-huh.

95
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:43,220
- Quentin! Oh!
- Hey. Ha ha!

96
00:03:43,222 --> 00:03:44,588
Oh, so good
to see you.

97
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:46,190
And you, too.

98
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:48,058
I saw your interview
with the dragon lady,

99
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:49,893
and you nailed it.

100
00:03:49,895 --> 00:03:51,395
Uh, that's his girlfriend
you're talking about there.

101
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:55,199
<b><font color="#FF8000">Thea:</font></b> Yes.
Uh, don't remind me.

102
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,068
What are you doing here?

103
00:04:00,239 --> 00:04:03,307
You, uh, prosecuting
him for something?

104
00:04:03,309 --> 00:04:06,076
Uh, actually, Quentin
was just introducing us.

105
00:04:06,078 --> 00:04:08,545
I'm the new deputy
mayor's assistant.

106
00:04:08,547 --> 00:04:10,848
<font color="#D900D9">[Clears throat]</font>

107
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:12,349
I, uh...

108
00:04:12,351 --> 00:04:14,484
never should have left.

109
00:04:14,486 --> 00:04:17,020
Well, uh, talking
of leaving,

110
00:04:17,022 --> 00:04:18,722
I got to get across town
for an alderman meeting.

111
00:04:18,724 --> 00:04:20,657
<b><font color="#FF8000">Rene:</font></b> Uh, you need me
to come with?

112
00:04:20,659 --> 00:04:23,527
Nice try, but those
regulatory forms

113
00:04:23,529 --> 00:04:25,696
are not gonna fill
themselves out.

114
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:41,445
<b><font color="#FF8000">Adrian:</font></b> I'm just saying
that maybe you could get

115
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:43,013
Susan Williams to back off.

116
00:04:43,015 --> 00:04:44,748
Bottom line--I'm not
comfortable leveraging

117
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:47,317
a personal relationship
for political gain.

118
00:04:47,319 --> 00:04:49,386
The media's right, man.

119
00:04:49,388 --> 00:04:51,121
You're not much of
a politician.

120
00:04:51,123 --> 00:04:52,923
As it is, I'm not
comfortable covering up

121
00:04:52,925 --> 00:04:54,191
the circumstances
surrounding

122
00:04:54,193 --> 00:04:55,459
the death of
Detective Malone.

123
00:04:55,461 --> 00:04:56,727
So maybe
if Susan Williams--

124
00:04:56,729 --> 00:04:58,395
<font color="#804040">Man:</font> Mister--Mr. Mayor!

125
00:04:58,397 --> 00:04:59,696
- There's a shooter in the building.
- What? Wait--

126
00:04:59,698 --> 00:05:01,598
we need to get you to
a secure locat--

127
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,133
<font color="#0CEC0C">[gunfire, explosions]</font>

128
00:05:03,135 --> 00:05:05,469
<font color="#D900D9">[Woman moans]</font>

129
00:05:27,793 --> 00:05:29,559
<font color="#D900D9">[Indistinct shouting]</font>

130
00:05:41,907 --> 00:05:43,440
<font color="#804040">Woman, voice-over:</font>
Rene Ramirez,

131
00:05:43,442 --> 00:05:44,708
you are a dead man.

132
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:46,343
Zoe's gonna totally kill you

133
00:05:46,345 --> 00:05:48,111
if you guys
are late to the game.

134
00:05:50,349 --> 00:05:52,115
<font color="#D900D9">[Chuckling]</font>
What?

135
00:05:52,117 --> 00:05:55,719
No way we'll be late,
not the way I drive.

136
00:05:55,721 --> 00:05:57,988
<font color="#D900D9">[Both chuckle]</font>

137
00:05:57,990 --> 00:06:00,390
Whoo! Ok.

138
00:06:02,194 --> 00:06:03,460
Whoa.

139
00:06:03,462 --> 00:06:05,128
What do you think
you're doing?

140
00:06:05,130 --> 00:06:06,763
Stadium's
in the Glades, babe,

141
00:06:06,765 --> 00:06:09,299
in like the worst part of
the worst part of town.

142
00:06:09,301 --> 00:06:10,600
<font color="#D900D9">[Scoffs]</font>

143
00:06:10,602 --> 00:06:12,202
I brought it with me
last time I took Zoe.

144
00:06:12,204 --> 00:06:14,738
So you're admitting
you broke the rule?

145
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:16,373
Kind of what I do, babe.

146
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:17,774
The only reason I agree

147
00:06:17,776 --> 00:06:19,409
to let you keep that
thing in the house is

148
00:06:19,411 --> 00:06:21,445
because you said we needed it
for home protection.

149
00:06:21,447 --> 00:06:24,147
- Right back--
- as in, stays in the home.

150
00:06:24,149 --> 00:06:25,382
Now, hurry up.

151
00:06:25,384 --> 00:06:27,617
You guys are
gonna be late.

152
00:06:27,619 --> 00:06:30,020
I thought we were
going as a family.

153
00:06:30,022 --> 00:06:31,221
<font color="#D900D9">[Sighs]</font>

154
00:06:31,223 --> 00:06:32,389
I have a headache.

155
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:35,125
Oh, yeah?
You been taking

156
00:06:35,127 --> 00:06:36,994
something stronger than
aspirin for that headache?

157
00:06:36,996 --> 00:06:40,430
You got something you
want to say to me, Rene?

158
00:06:40,432 --> 00:06:43,000
I guess I do.

159
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:44,568
Using again?

160
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:45,936
<font color="#0CEC0C">[Gunfire]</font>

161
00:06:50,542 --> 00:06:52,843
<font color="#804040">Guard:</font> The shooter's Mia.
He's exited the building.

162
00:06:52,845 --> 00:06:54,044
<b><font color="#FF8000">Oliver:</font></b>
Alert the SCPD and the ACU.

163
00:06:54,046 --> 00:06:55,746
Drop a 5-block net
around city hall.

164
00:06:55,748 --> 00:06:57,381
Let's get ambulances here
immediately!

165
00:06:57,383 --> 00:07:00,050
And has anyone seen
my sister?!

166
00:07:01,086 --> 00:07:02,319
Ollie.

167
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:03,620
Hey, are you all right?
Are you ok?

168
00:07:03,622 --> 00:07:05,288
Adrian!

169
00:07:05,290 --> 00:07:07,357
<font color="#D900D9">[Overlapping conversations]</font>

170
00:07:19,571 --> 00:07:21,070
You're gonna be ok.

171
00:07:21,072 --> 00:07:23,072
Just catch this
son of a bitch.

172
00:07:23,074 --> 00:07:24,941
Yeah. Go on.

173
00:07:24,943 --> 00:07:26,943
<font color="#0CEC0C">[Sirens, police radio chatter]</font>

174
00:07:36,654 --> 00:07:38,254
How many casualties?

175
00:07:38,256 --> 00:07:40,089
There's 5 dead, 24 injured,

176
00:07:40,091 --> 00:07:42,525
and 8 in critical condition.

177
00:07:42,527 --> 00:07:44,060
The bastard
was wearing Kevlar,

178
00:07:44,062 --> 00:07:45,728
but I think one of my shots
went into his shoulder

179
00:07:45,730 --> 00:07:47,263
with a 9-mil slug.

180
00:07:47,265 --> 00:07:49,665
Might be a good idea to alert
all the emergency rooms?

181
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:51,300
Do it.

182
00:07:51,302 --> 00:07:52,869
What were you doing
with a gun in here?

183
00:07:52,871 --> 00:07:54,270
Judging by
how I tagged the guy,

184
00:07:54,272 --> 00:07:56,239
I got to go with saving
people's lives.

185
00:07:56,241 --> 00:07:57,907
Your security detail
said

186
00:07:57,909 --> 00:07:59,442
the shooter dropped
his primary weapon.

187
00:07:59,444 --> 00:08:01,411
We need to get it
before the police do.

188
00:08:01,413 --> 00:08:03,212
I took care of it.

189
00:08:04,549 --> 00:08:06,916
This is military-grade
hardware.

190
00:08:06,918 --> 00:08:08,751
AR-15 assault weapon.

191
00:08:08,753 --> 00:08:10,820
It fires 5.56 NATO rounds.

192
00:08:10,822 --> 00:08:14,457
It's an M16. It's literally
the same gun as an M16.

193
00:08:14,459 --> 00:08:15,725
Seems like some of
Tobias Church's

194
00:08:15,727 --> 00:08:17,627
ordnance got into
the wrong hand--

195
00:08:17,629 --> 00:08:19,395
wronger hands.

196
00:08:19,397 --> 00:08:21,264
Not necessarily.
It's an AR-15.

197
00:08:21,266 --> 00:08:23,032
It's available on
the open market.

198
00:08:23,034 --> 00:08:25,468
In fact, it's the most popular gun
in America.

199
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:28,638
The land of the free, home
of the incredibly stupid.

200
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,106
We are not having
this conversation now

201
00:08:30,108 --> 00:08:31,274
or ever, guys.

202
00:08:31,276 --> 00:08:32,909
<b><font color="#FF8000">Oliver:</font></b> Where are
we with the gun?

203
00:08:32,911 --> 00:08:34,911
Nowhere. It hasn't been
used in any prior crime.

204
00:08:34,913 --> 00:08:36,512
<b><font color="#FF8000">Oliver:</font></b>
Fingerprints?

205
00:08:36,514 --> 00:08:38,081
The shooter wasn't
wearing gloves.

206
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:39,582
AFIS didn't
kick back anything.

207
00:08:39,584 --> 00:08:40,817
I don't think he's ever
been in the system.

208
00:08:40,819 --> 00:08:42,118
Or he was
smart enough

209
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,619
to have himself
erased from it.

210
00:08:43,621 --> 00:08:45,054
Security cameras.

211
00:08:45,056 --> 00:08:46,789
He knew how to avoid them.

212
00:08:46,791 --> 00:08:49,425
And before he opened fire,
he upgraded to a ski mask.

213
00:08:49,427 --> 00:08:51,828
That looks like
a utility jumpsuit.

214
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:52,995
Forefather Repair.

215
00:08:52,997 --> 00:08:54,197
It went belly up
6 years ago.

216
00:08:54,199 --> 00:08:55,631
I ran through
the employee list,

217
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:57,200
but I think our shooter
just bought a uniform

218
00:08:57,202 --> 00:08:58,367
off the Internet.

219
00:08:58,369 --> 00:09:00,169
So he could walk
into city hall.

220
00:09:00,171 --> 00:09:01,404
This guy's real good at
covering his tracks,

221
00:09:01,406 --> 00:09:02,972
whoever he is.

222
00:09:02,974 --> 00:09:04,273
So who is he?

223
00:09:04,275 --> 00:09:06,142
<b><font color="#FF8000">Quentin:</font></b> Yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

224
00:09:06,144 --> 00:09:08,111
That--there.
Yeah, that's the guy.

225
00:09:08,113 --> 00:09:10,480
Run him through
the system for me, would you?

226
00:09:10,482 --> 00:09:12,348
Hey, this is
where you've been.

227
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:13,950
I think I got a look
at the shooter

228
00:09:13,952 --> 00:09:15,518
before he put his
ski mask on.

229
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,653
I let that
son of a bitch

230
00:09:17,655 --> 00:09:19,155
walk right past me.

231
00:09:19,157 --> 00:09:20,723
Hey, you couldn't
have known, Hoss.

232
00:09:20,725 --> 00:09:22,225
Listen, I've been police
most of my adult life.

233
00:09:22,227 --> 00:09:23,526
I should've been able
to spot that guy

234
00:09:23,528 --> 00:09:24,827
a thousand yards out.

235
00:09:24,829 --> 00:09:26,529
Hey, don't go there,
man, all right?

236
00:09:26,531 --> 00:09:28,731
What happened wasn't
your fault.

237
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:30,833
I heard you got
a few shots off.

238
00:09:30,835 --> 00:09:32,335
Yeah. And I would've
put him down, too,

239
00:09:32,337 --> 00:09:33,903
if he wasn't wearing
body armor.

240
00:09:33,905 --> 00:09:35,738
Listen, weren't you
dishonorably discharged?

241
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:37,406
Not for my aim, Hoss.

242
00:09:37,408 --> 00:09:40,376
My point is it's illegal
for someone such as yourself

243
00:09:40,378 --> 00:09:42,044
to carry a firearm.

244
00:09:42,046 --> 00:09:43,446
But it's pretty easy
to buy one, though.

245
00:09:43,448 --> 00:09:44,747
